'''

'''
import json
import java.io
from org.apache.commons.io import IOUtils
from java.nio.charset import StandardCharsets
from org.apache.nifi.processor.io import StreamCallback
from collections import OrderedDict

class PyStreamCallback(StreamCallback):
    def __init__(self, flowFile):
        self.ff = flowFile
        pass
    
    def process(self, inputStream, outputStream):
        inputText = IOUtils.toString(inputStream, StandardCharsets.UTF_8)
        outputErrorMessage = OrderedDict()
        
        #Source Batch Id 
        sourceBatchId = self.ff.getAttribute("batchId")
        if sourceBatchId:
            outputErrorMessage["sourceBatchId"] = sourceBatchId
        
        #Notification Batch Id 
        notificationBatchId = self.ff.getAttribute("outgoingBatchId")
        if notificationBatchId:
            outputErrorMessage["notificationBatchId"] = notificationBatchId
        
        #Batch Name 
        batchName = self.ff.getAttribute("batchName")
        if batchName:
            outputErrorMessage["name"] = batchName        
            
        #DataType  
        dataType = self.ff.getAttribute("dataType")
        if dataType:
            outputErrorMessage["dataType"] = dataType        

        #FHIR Resource id  
        fhirResourceId = self.ff.getAttribute("resourceId")
        if fhirResourceId:
            outputErrorMessage["fhirResourceId"] = fhirResourceId        

        #FHIR Resource Type  
        fhirResourceType = self.ff.getAttribute("resourceType")
        if fhirResourceType:
            outputErrorMessage["fhirResourceType"] = fhirResourceType        

        #Bundle Resource id  
        bundleResourceId = self.ff.getAttribute("bundleId")
        if bundleResourceId:
            outputErrorMessage["bundleResourceId"] = bundleResourceId        

        #Bundle Entry Index  
        bundleEntryIndex = self.ff.getAttribute("fragment.index")
        if bundleEntryIndex:
            outputErrorMessage["bundleEntryIndex"] = bundleEntryIndex        

        # Adapter name
        outputErrorMessage["adapterName"] = "Interop FHIR Adapter"
        
        #FHIR Resource Tag  
        fhirResourceTag = self.ff.getAttribute("FHIRResourceTag")
        if fhirResourceTag:
            outputErrorMessage["fhirResourceTag"] = fhirResourceTag        

        #Status Code
        statusCode = self.ff.getAttribute("invokehttp.status.code")
        if statusCode:
            outputErrorMessage["statusCode"] = statusCode
            
        #Status Message
        statusMessage = self.ff.getAttribute("invokehttp.status.message")
        if statusMessage:
            outputErrorMessage["statusMessage"] = statusMessage
            
        # Error Details
        if inputText:
            operationOutcomeResource = json.loads(inputText, object_pairs_hook=OrderedDict)
            if "issue" in operationOutcomeResource:
                newIssues = []
           
                for anIssue in operationOutcomeResource["issue"]:
                    if anIssue["severity"] != "information":
                        newIssues.append(anIssue)

                if len(newIssues) != 0:
                    operationOutcomeResource["issue"] = newIssues
            
            outputErrorMessage["errorDetails"] = operationOutcomeResource
        
        outputStream.write(bytearray(json.dumps(outputErrorMessage, indent=4).encode("utf-8")))

flowFile = session.get()
flowFile = session.write(flowFile, PyStreamCallback(flowFile))
    
session.transfer(flowFile, REL_SUCCESS)
session.commit()

properties.Script Body:
'''
 IBM Confidential
 OCO Source Materials
 
 (c) Copyright IBM Corp. 2020
 
 The source code for this program is not published or otherwise divested
 of its trade secrets, irrespective of what has been deposited with the
 U.S. Copyright Office.
'''
import json
import java.io
from org.apache.commons.io import IOUtils
from java.nio.charset import StandardCharsets
from org.apache.nifi.processor.io import StreamCallback
from collections import OrderedDict

class PyStreamCallback(StreamCallback):
    def __init__(self):
        pass
    
    def process(self, inputStream, outputStream):
        inputText = IOUtils.toString(inputStream, StandardCharsets.UTF_8)
        inputFHIRResource = json.loads(inputText, object_pairs_hook=OrderedDict)

        # need to rebuild the resource bundle with type transaction.
        outputFHIRResource = OrderedDict()

        if inputFHIRResource["resourceType"] == "Bundle":
            # recreate the bundle resource  
            outputFHIRResource["resourceType"] = "Bundle"
            outputFHIRResource["type"] = "transaction"
    
            if "id" in inputFHIRResource:
                outputFHIRResource["id"] = inputFHIRResource["id"]
    
            # build the new entry list by grabbing the resource and setting the request
            newEntryList = []
            for anEntry in inputFHIRResource["entry"]:                    
                newEntry = OrderedDict()
                isDeleteEntry = False
                
                if "request" in anEntry:
                    requestEntry = anEntry["request"]
                    if requestEntry["method"] == "DELETE":
                        newEntry["request"] = requestEntry
                        isDeleteEntry = True
                
                if not isDeleteEntry:    
                    newEntry ["resource"] = anEntry["resource"]
        
                    requestEntry = OrderedDict()
                    resourceType = newEntry["resource"] ["resourceType"]
        
                    if "id" in newEntry["resource"]:
                        requestEntry = {"method": "PUT", "url": resourceType + '/' + newEntry["resource"] ["id"]}
                    else:
                        requestEntry = {"method": "POST", "url": resourceType}
            
                    newEntry["request"] = requestEntry
            
                newEntryList.append(newEntry)

            outputFHIRResource["entry"] = newEntryList
        else:
            # not a resource bundle, just pass it along
            outputFHIRResource = inputFHIRResource

        outputStream.write(bytearray(json.dumps(outputFHIRResource, indent=4).encode("utf-8")))

flowFile = session.get()
if (flowFile != None):
    flowFile = session.write(flowFile, PyStreamCallback())
    flowFile = session.putAttribute(flowFile, "filename", flowFile.getAttribute('filename').split('.')[0] + '_updated.json')
    
session.transfer(flowFile, REL_SUCCESS)
session.commit()

processGroups.name: Resolve Terminology
FHIR Terminology Mapping
Translate Codes
Extract Bundle Extensions
processGroups.comments:
Input:
FHIR Bundles

Output:
1) The original FHIR Bundles with the corresponding fragment.identifier and fragment.counts attributes based on the number of "extensions" that were extracted from each.

2) The individual "extension" JSON object extracted from each Bundle, with their corresponding fragment.identifier and fragment.index so that they can be matched against the Bundle where they came from.

3) The resulting flow files will include a couple of attributes: "url" with the extension "URL" field, and "code" with the extension "valueCode" field. If the extension is not of type "valueCode" it will still be output but the attribute will be empty.

4) The actual JSON extension text will also be included as an attribute called "extension"

processors.name: Extract Extension URL & Code
Extract Bundle Extensions
processors.comments:
A FHIR Bundle may have multiple FHIR Resources (e.g. Patient, Observation, Encounter, MedicationRequest, etc.) and each of those FHIR Resources may have multiple "extensions". Some of those extensions may need to be translated. This processor extracts all of those extensions and sends the off to processing. 

This processor additionally sends the original files from where the extensions were obtained to Wait, until all of the extensions from each FHIR Bundle are processed.

processGroups.name: Persist Bundle
processGroups.comments:
Input:
A FHIR Bundle

Output:
- The FHIR Bundle persisted in the file system in NIFI_HOME/temp/terminology-flow/{uuid}
- An attribute set with the bundle identifier bundle.identifier.
- An attribute called "translated" set to false

processors.name: Save Original Bundle File
processors.comments:
The original FHIR bundle needs to be saved to the file system, because it may be too large to carry over as an Attribute, and we will need to carry over the transformation as flowfiles. We save it to the file system and we will pull it out when we need to modify it.

This processor saves the incoming bundle to the NIFI_HOME/temp/terminology-flow/{uuid}

processors.name: Set Bundle Identifier
processors.comments:
Each FHIR Bundle that comes in will be identified by its unique ID. We can use the existing UUID of the flowfile that contains the bundle. We need to save it to its own attribute because the flowfile will eventually change, and with that the UUID of the flowfiles will change, but we need to be able to reference the FHIR bundle that we saved in the previous step.

This processor will save the ID of this bundle in an attribute called bundle.identifier.

processGroups.name: Get Matching ConceptMap
processGroups.comments:
Input:
- An extension flow file that has the "url" attribute for its corresponding StructureDefinition

Output:
- The ID of the ConceptMap that should be used to translate this extension from its current valueSet to a different valueSet. This ID will be in an attribute called "conceptMapID"
- An attribute "valueSet" which will include the ValueSet for the StructureDefinition in the "url"

processors.name: Get ConceptMap ID
processors.comments: Extracts the ConceptMapID into a n attribute called "conceptMapID"

processors.name: Adjust MIME Type
processors.comments:
The Content Type out of the FHIR server is set to 'application/fhir+json', which is not recognized by NiFi as just JSON.
This processor updates the MIME type attribute so that the JSON can be viewed with the NiFi file viewer.

In passing, this processor also updates the `filename` attribute so it's no longer called patients.json instead it will be called patient.json.

processors.name: Get ValueSet from StructureDefinition
processors.comments:
FHIR Extension objects have a URL and some value. The URL points to the StructureDefinition that describes the extension, more details here: https://www.hl7.org/fhir/extensibility.html

This Processor will look the StructureDefinition in a Map. That Map will have the mappings from StructureDefinition to ValueSet to query.

processors.name: Query ConceptMap for ValueSet
processors.comments:
Query the FHIR server for the ConceptMap whose source value set is the value set in the ${valueSet} attribute.
This attribute was obtained by mapping the StructureDefinition to a ValueSet.
